sf_chart: Variants

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
You can adapt these charts to your known utilization patterns. For example you can change the duration over which resource utilization is considered, or the thresholds that determine whether cpu, disk, or memory are considered underutilized.

In place of a 30 day time window (above) you may calculate average utilization over a week (on the right) or keep 30 days but change the definition of underutilized CPU from below-50% to below-25% (on the left).

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
RI Expiry


These charts identify Reservations that are closest to expiry, and list the instance counts and amortized costs by Reservation.

sf_chart: Days until RIs Expire
sf_description: Days until the RIs identified by their reserved_instance_ids expire.

sf_chart: Amount Lost in Unused RIs
sf_description: Calculation based on current unused RIs.

sf_chart: Days Until Next RI Expires
sf_description: Days remaining until the closest-to-expiry RI expires.

sf_chart: Normalized RI Coverage by Instance Family
sf_description: RI coverage in running instances, normalized to the small unit of the instance family.

sf_chart: RI Utilization
sf_description: Percentage of purchased reservations applied to running instances.

sf_chart: Unused Regional Reservations by Family (Normalized to Small Unit of the Instance Family)
sf_description: Chart may be blank if there are no unused reservations of scope Region. Reports unused reservations based on instance size flexibility (https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-instance-size-flexibility-for-ec2-reserved-instances/).

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
RI Coverage


These charts list running On-Demand instances, show estimated savings from purchasing reservations for them, and calculate RI coverage.
Many plots in this dashboard cannot be meaningfully filtered by AWS tags because of the way AWS applies reservations. You can filter as usual by other properties.

sf_chart: Instance Count by Reservation
sf_description: Count of instances in each reservation (identified by reserved_instance_id).

sf_chart: Normalized RI Coverage (%)
sf_description: Mean of RI coverage in running instances (normalized to the small unit of each instance family).

sf_chart: Amortized Monthly Cost of Reservations
sf_description: Amounts shown reflect amortization of any upfront costs.

sf_chart: On-Demand Instances (Normalized Count)
sf_description: Normalized to the small unit of each instance family (useful for flexible RI conversion - https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/new-instance-size-flexibility-for-ec2-reserved-instances/)

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
RI Utilization


These charts identify reservations that have been purchased but are not being used, and estimate wasted cost.

sf_chart: Unused Regional Reservations by Instance Type
sf_description: Chart may be blank if there are no unused reservations of scope Zone.

sf_chart: Potential Savings
sf_description: From purchasing reservations (assuming 3 Year No-Upfront Convertibles) for running On-Demand instances

sf_chart: Normalized RI Coverage
sf_description: Mean of RI coverage  in running instances (normalized to the small unit of each instance family).

sf_chart: RI Utilization (%) Over Time
sf_description: Percentage of RIs that are getting used in running instances.

sf_chart: Instances Terminated in the Last Seven Days
RI and On-Demand Instance Count
sf_description: Count of running Reserved Instances (green) and On-demand Instances (purple) - helps spot trends and relative changes.

sf_chart: Costs by Usage Type and EC2 Instance Type ($/minute)
sf_description: Filtering by instance type (available as a dashboard variable at the top) shows the spread of costs among  running On-Demand, running Reserved, and unused Reserved Instances.

allPlots.name: Count of Running Instances with RIs Applied

sf_description: Helps with eye-balling the distribution of EC2 Instances of a type across different AZ's

sf_chart: Total EC2 Cost per Day Including Unused Reservations (Extrapolated)
sf_description: Includes amortized costs from all unused reservations - helps spot trends and changes.

sf_uiModel.markdownText:
EC2 Worksheet


These charts are useful for exploring changes in your EC2 costs, usage, and RI Coverage.
Many plots in this dashboard cannot be meaningfully filtered by AWS tags. You can filter as usual by other properties.

sf_chart: RI and On-Demand Cost per Day (Exrapolated)
sf_description: Cost per day incurred running Reserved Instances (green) and On-demand Instances (purple) - helps spot trends and relative changes.

sf_chart: Count of Running Instances by Instance Type
Counts by Usage Type and EC2 Instance Type
sf_description: Filtering by instance type (available as a dashboard variable at the top) shows the spread among running On-Demand, running Reserved, and unused Reserved Instances.

sf_chart: RI and On-Demand Cost per Day (Extrapolated)
sf_description: Cost of running Reserved Instances includes loss from unused reservations.

sf_chart: Instances Started in the Last Seven Days
Total EC2 Cost per Day Including Unused Reservations (Extrapolated)
sf_description: Includes amortized costs from all unused reservations.
